          <p>We see that the additive effect at the marker SNP decreases linearly with <italic>r</italic> as the LD becomes weaker. This is a key result: it gives an intuitive and convenient relationship between the parameters of interest. Furthermore, the relationship later derived for the effect of LD on power follows directly from it. In this formulation, this result appears to be novel.</p>
