            </disp-formula>
          </p>
          <p>and</p>
          <p>
            <disp-formula>
              <graphic xlink:href="gepi0035-0278-m32"/>
            </disp-formula>
          </p>
          <p>Thus, a sample size of <italic>N</italic><sub><italic>B</italic></sub> = <italic>N</italic><sub><italic>A</italic></sub>/<italic>r</italic><sup>4</sup> is required to achieve the same power as typing the causal SNP directly.</p>
        </sec>
        <sec>
          <title>Interaction test</title>
          <p>The Wald test for the interaction parameter compares our interaction model to a two-SNP multiplicative model; we refer to this as the <italic>interaction</italic> test. Using Equations (12) and (<xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="m28">7</xref>) gives the noncentrality parameters,</p>
